Note that if a CastDevice cannot be yet discovered, you can still create one manually with this hack (here, for cast-android-sample. Replace ip and Uri with correct values ):
``` java
try {
            mSelectedDevice = new CastDevice((Inet4Address)InetAddress.getByName("192.168.0.13"));
        mSelectedDevice.setFriendlyName("LOL Cast");
        mSelectedDevice.setModelName("ChromeCast");
        mSelectedDevice.setManufacturer("LOL company");

            Field f = CastDevice.class.getDeclaredField("f");
        if (f != null) {
                f.setAccessible(true);
            f.set(mSelectedDevice, Uri.parse("http://192.168.0.13:8008/apps"));
            logVIfEnabled(TAG, "Successfully set Application URL");
        }

        onDeviceAvailable(mSelectedDevice, "LOL", null);
    } catch (Exception e) {
        e.printStackTrace();
    }

